text: The MFF Ooredoo Cup 2014 was the 2014 edition of the MFF Cup. The winner qualified for the 2015 AFC Cup. A total of 22 teams entered the competition. ==First round== Draw held on 31 March 2014. Matches played on 5 and 6 April 2014. |} ==Second round== Draw held on 2 May 2014. Matches played on 7, 8 and 9 May 2014. |} ==Third round== Draw held on 30 June 2014.MFF Ooredoo Cup to hold third round matches Matches played on 5, 6 and 7 July 2014. |} ==Quarter- finals== Matches played on 20 and 21 July 2014.Nay Pyi Taw through to semis on penalties, Yangon booted out |} ==Semi-finals== Matches played on 6 August 2014.Nay Pyi Taw set Ooredoo Cup final date with Ayeyawady |} ==Final== Final played on 21 September 2014. ==References== ==External links== *MFF Ooredoo Cup Category:General Aung San Shield Cup Burma
title: 2014 MFF Cup
